01:02:19,336 --> 01:02:22,270
Yep...

1047
01:02:22,272 --> 01:02:23,939
I'm real happy
about my decision

1048
01:02:23,941 --> 01:02:25,173
to stick with you guys.

1049
01:02:26,744 --> 01:02:31,279
Uh, at the risk of
rekindling hostilities,

1050
01:02:31,281 --> 01:02:34,883
what do we do now?

1051
01:02:34,885 --> 01:02:37,986
Like I said,
have a little faith.

1052
01:03:09,520 --> 01:03:11,419
¶ Ha ha ha ha ¶

1053
01:03:19,963 --> 01:03:21,530
Is that my ears,
or has your singing

1054
01:03:21,532 --> 01:03:22,931
actually gotten worse?

1055
01:03:22,933 --> 01:03:24,332
Must be your ears.

1056
01:03:24,334 --> 01:03:26,468
It was as bad
as it already could be!

1057
01:03:26,470 --> 01:03:29,471
Doyle: Have
a little faith, my eye.

1058
01:03:29,473 --> 01:03:31,373
You knew this boat was coming.

1059
01:03:31,375 --> 01:03:33,909
My first tour, I was
stationed at hau bon.

1060
01:03:33,911 --> 01:03:35,477
Every Wednesday afternoon,

1061
01:03:35,479 --> 01:03:38,280
monsieur Goddard and the<i> Marie
antoinette</i> would drop in.

1062
01:03:38,282 --> 01:03:40,448
He gave us
the best intelligence

1063
01:03:40,450 --> 01:03:43,318
on the location of the v.C.
We ever got.

1064
01:03:43,320 --> 01:03:44,920
What... what can I say?
I love America.

1065
01:03:44,922 --> 01:03:46,988
Yeah. Hey.

1066
01:03:49,560 --> 01:03:51,960
You gave the v.C.
Their best intelligence

1067
01:03:51,962 --> 01:03:53,562
on our location, too.

1068
01:03:54,898 --> 01:03:55,997
I can't help it, you know.

1069
01:03:55,999 --> 01:03:57,365
I love everybody.

1070
01:03:57,367 --> 01:03:58,533
Would anyone
like some wine here?

1071
01:03:58,535 --> 01:03:59,835
Yeah. Yeah.

1072
01:03:59,837 --> 01:04:01,369
Wine?! No!

1073
01:04:01,371 --> 01:04:03,271
What is this, the opening
of an art gallery?!

1074
01:04:03,273 --> 01:04:04,873
No. This is a war.

1075
01:04:04,875 --> 01:04:06,908
The green beret motto
is "free the oppressed,"

1076
01:04:06,910 --> 01:04:08,376
not "eat, drink, and be merry."

1077
01:04:08,378 --> 01:04:09,477
Yeah, now it is.

1078
01:04:09,479 --> 01:04:11,379
Aww.

1079
01:04:11,381 --> 01:04:14,382
What did I do? What did I do?!

1080
01:04:14,384 --> 01:04:16,251
I should be on some
high-priority mission

1081
01:04:16,253 --> 01:04:17,953
with a group
of crack commandos.

1082
01:04:17,955 --> 01:04:19,921
Instead, I'm in an episode
of<i> mchale's Navy,</i>

1083
01:04:19,923 --> 01:04:22,591
starring dumbo, Mr. French,
and the 3 stooges!

1084
01:04:31,635 --> 01:04:33,902
<i>D'ng lai.</i>

1085
01:04:33,904 --> 01:04:35,237
That mean stop.

1086
01:04:35,239 --> 01:04:37,406
<i>D'ng lai?</i>

1087
01:04:37,407 --> 01:04:39,574
<i>Dee.</i> That mean go.

1088
01:04:39,576 --> 01:04:41,243
<i>Dee?</i>

1089
01:04:41,245 --> 01:04:43,578
You try.

1090
01:04:43,580 --> 01:04:45,447
<i>Dee!</i>

1091
01:04:46,483 --> 01:04:48,917
Uh... d-d-d... uh... uh...

1092
01:04:48,919 --> 01:04:49,885
<i>D'ng lai!</i>

1093
01:04:49,887 --> 01:04:51,219
Good.

1094
01:04:51,221 --> 01:04:52,921
You know 2 of 3
most important words

1095
01:04:52,923 --> 01:04:54,289
for elephant.

1096
01:04:54,291 --> 01:04:56,024
What's the third?

1097
01:04:57,327 --> 01:04:58,360
Huh?

1098
01:04:58,362 --> 01:04:59,995
It means get off me.

1099
01:05:02,299 --> 01:05:03,331
Poole.

1100
01:05:05,402 --> 01:05:07,502
Can you get more of that
water buffalo tranquilizer?

1101
01:05:07,504 --> 01:05:09,471
You really enjoyed that,
didn't you, Doyle?

1102
01:05:12,309 --> 01:05:13,909
Linh was right.

1103
01:05:13,911 --> 01:05:15,010
You are weird.

1104
01:05:15,012 --> 01:05:16,478
Poole.

1105
01:05:16,480 --> 01:05:18,013
Poole: Yeah, yeah.

1106
01:05:18,015 --> 01:05:18,980
As much as you want.

1107
01:05:18,982 --> 01:05:21,283
Ok.

1108
01:05:21,285 --> 01:05:23,351
We get off past
hau bon tonight.

1109
01:05:23,353 --> 01:05:25,387
Tomorrow we take
one of these trails

1110
01:05:25,389 --> 01:05:26,454
which, God willing,

1111
01:05:26,456 --> 01:05:27,923
isn't in enemy hands,

1112
01:05:27,925 --> 01:05:28,957
over one of these ridges,

1113
01:05:28,959 --> 01:05:30,692
down into pleiku.

1114
01:05:30,694 --> 01:05:32,460
Friday morning we fly Bo-tat

1115
01:05:32,462 --> 01:05:34,462
to the airstrip
near the village.

1116
01:05:34,464 --> 01:05:36,932
By noon we walk her in.

1117
01:05:36,934 --> 01:05:37,933
Piece of cake.

1118
01:05:41,338 --> 01:05:43,305
Get down!

1119
01:05:50,681 --> 01:05:53,014
Doyle: Stay down!
Everyone stay down!

1120
01:05:57,020 --> 01:05:59,020
Farley. Hold your fire.

1121
01:05:59,022 --> 01:06:01,289
They're out of range.

1122
01:06:04,027 --> 01:06:06,294
They're gonna have us
in 5 rounds.

1123
01:06:06,296 --> 01:06:07,696
I know this. I'm artillery.

1124
01:06:09,032 --> 01:06:11,399
Give them a moving target.
Zigzag.

1125
01:06:20,010 --> 01:06:21,409
Keep moving.

1126
01:06:36,760 --> 01:06:38,693
Linh, what's wrong with Bo-tat?

1127
01:06:38,695 --> 01:06:40,562
She hurt here.

1128
01:06:40,564 --> 01:06:42,030
Oh, sh...

1129
01:06:42,032 --> 01:06:43,698
oh, no, she's seasick.

1130
01:06:47,037 --> 01:06:48,403
Look out... she's gonna blow!

1131
01:06:48,405 --> 01:06:49,404
Eww!

1132
01:06:58,248 --> 01:06:59,714
Years from now
my kid's gonna ask me,

1133
01:06:59,716 --> 01:07:02,317
"daddy, what's the worst
thing you saw in the war?"

1134
01:07:02,319 --> 01:07:03,752
After this, there's no contest.

1135
01:07:12,496 --> 01:07:14,396
Doyle: Can't you get this
tub to go any faster?!

1136
01:07:16,066 --> 01:07:18,333
You are going to sink my boat.

1137
01:07:19,736 --> 01:07:21,603
Maybe not.

1138
01:07:26,777 --> 01:07:28,476
Gilman, who would
I actually know

1139
01:07:28,478 --> 01:07:29,611
that could get me
your head in a bag?

1140
01:07:29,613 --> 01:07:30,745
It was a joke, pal.

1141
01:07:30,747 --> 01:07:33,048
Yeah, I was kidding.

1142
01:07:33,050 --> 01:07:35,050
I love you, man.
Like a brother.

1143
01:07:35,052 --> 01:07:36,618
What are you, nuts?!

1144
01:07:36,620 --> 01:07:38,470
Where am I gonna find
a triumph spitfire

1145
01:07:38,471 --> 01:07:40,321
in the middle of Vietnam,
you rotten little rat?!

1146
01:07:40,323 --> 01:07:42,323
Ok, ok, I'm sorry. I apologize.

1147
01:07:42,325 --> 01:07:46,061
Ok. All right, you got it.

1148
01:07:46,063 --> 01:07:47,695
Just patch me through to
firebase cheo reo now, ok?

1149
01:07:47,697 --> 01:07:49,064
And direct to artillery.

1150
01:07:49,066 --> 01:07:50,598
I don't have time
for channels or anything.

1151
01:07:50,600 --> 01:07:52,634
Ok. He's puttin' me through.

1152
01:07:52,636 --> 01:07:55,503
Son of a... heh heh.
Right here. Hang on.

1153
01:07:58,075 --> 01:07:59,274
Uh... Yeah...

1154
01:07:59,276 --> 01:08:00,775
We're on the song ba river

1155
01:08:00,777 --> 01:08:03,344
being pursued
by n.V.A. In a boat.

1156
01:08:03,346 --> 01:08:05,613
What? Yeah,
this is hotel Alpha.

1157
01:08:05,615 --> 01:08:07,515
Who's this? Barney?

1158
01:08:07,517 --> 01:08:08,850
Hey, Barney, what's up, man?
What you doin'...

1159
01:08:08,852 --> 01:08:10,385
h.A.! H.A.! I'm sorry.

1160
01:08:10,387 --> 01:08:13,321
Uh, cheo reo, we
need your help pronto.

1161
01:08:13,323 --> 01:08:15,423
Request fire mission
and expedite.

1162
01:08:15,425 --> 01:08:16,791
Call for battery fire
at grid coordinates

1163
01:08:16,793 --> 01:08:20,428
bravo Romeo 354...1105 niner.

1164
01:08:20,430 --> 01:08:21,830
Fire one marking round.

1165
01:08:32,342 --> 01:08:33,641
Barney, that was perfect, man!

1166
01:08:33,643 --> 01:08:35,510
No, it wasn't perfect.
It almost hit us!

1167
01:08:35,512 --> 01:08:37,462
Give 'em other coordinates.

1168
01:08:37,463 --> 01:08:39,413
Captain, we're moving. Those
coordinates are gonna be perfect.

1169
01:08:39,416 --> 01:08:40,648
Right about... Better be right.

1170
01:08:40,650 --> 01:08:41,783
Fire for effect!

1171
01:08:41,785 --> 01:08:43,718
Better be right. Now.

1172
01:08:55,365 --> 01:08:58,633
Ha! Whoo! Whoa!

1173
01:08:58,635 --> 01:08:59,834
Yeah!

1174
01:08:59,836 --> 01:09:01,870
Hey, hey. I'm gonna
start callin' you

1175
01:09:01,872 --> 01:09:03,638
the brown bomber!
Ha ha ha ha ha!

1176
01:09:03,640 --> 01:09:05,440
Brown bomber.

1177
01:09:29,866 --> 01:09:32,367
You wanna try it on?

1178
01:09:49,886 --> 01:09:52,287
I found a place where
we can spend the night.

1179
01:10:27,891 --> 01:10:30,792
Farley: Hey, sir,
what is this place?

1180
01:10:30,794 --> 01:10:33,661
An ancient temple.

1181
01:10:33,663 --> 01:10:35,463
Buddhist?

1182
01:10:35,465 --> 01:10:38,533
Actually, it's tam giao.

1183
01:10:38,535 --> 01:10:42,904
A little buddhism, a little
confucianism, and a little tao.

1184
01:10:57,520 --> 01:10:59,654
What's with all the elephants?

1185
01:11:01,791 --> 01:11:04,425
The elephant
is the God in tam giao.

1186
01:11:05,762 --> 01:11:06,894
Not a God.

1187
01:11:06,896 --> 01:11:09,330
<i>Father</i> of God.

1188
01:11:11,368 --> 01:11:14,535
In beginning,
elephant were white,

1189
01:11:14,537 --> 01:11:17,805
and they fly in the air with
the clouds and the rain.

1190
01:11:20,810 --> 01:11:25,413
One day, elephant fly down and
go into side of queen Maya...

1191
01:11:25,415 --> 01:11:28,650
While she sleep and dream.

1192
01:11:28,652 --> 01:11:31,386
She have baby.

1193
01:11:31,388 --> 01:11:35,290
Prince siddhartha,
the gautama Buddha.

1194
01:11:35,292 --> 01:11:38,459
Elephant, father of God.

1195
01:12:07,490 --> 01:12:11,092
Linh, that story
you told was great.

1196
01:12:11,094 --> 01:12:12,860
I... I loved the bit
about the flying elephants.

1197
01:12:12,862 --> 01:12:15,730
Uh, just one thing, though.

1198
01:12:15,732 --> 01:12:17,832
It might be better if you
started, "in the beginning,

1199
01:12:17,834 --> 01:12:19,667
all elephants were black."

1200
01:12:20,770 --> 01:12:22,670
All right, this
is our only option.

1201
01:12:22,672 --> 01:12:26,541
We have to take this trail
over this pass into pleiku.

1202
01:12:26,543 --> 01:12:28,576
Is the pass secure?

1203
01:12:28,578 --> 01:12:30,845
Tch. I don't know.

1204
01:12:30,847 --> 01:12:32,680
We could find out
at this village

1205
01:12:32,682 --> 01:12:34,682
unless you think 5
Americans and an elephant

1206
01:12:34,684 --> 01:12:36,818
waltzing into town might
arouse suspicion.

1207
01:12:36,820 --> 01:12:38,586
Hmm. Not at all.

1208
01:12:38,588 --> 01:12:39,921
We could send in linh.

1209
01:12:39,923 --> 01:12:41,422
No one would suspect him.

1210
01:12:41,424 --> 01:12:42,590
No, we can't do that.

1211
01:12:42,592 --> 01:12:43,691
Why not?

1212
01:12:43,693 --> 01:12:44,692
You know why.

1213
01:12:44,694 --> 01:12:46,494
We can't take that chance.

1214
01:12:53,636 --> 01:12:55,737
I got it. Wait.

1215
01:13:23,900 --> 01:13:27,168
Doesn't matter to me
who killed your family.

1216
01:13:27,170 --> 01:13:29,704
I imagine it doesn't
matter to you, either.

1217
01:13:31,708 --> 01:13:35,476
V.C. Killed
mother and sister...

1218
01:13:35,478 --> 01:13:39,414
But linh not know
who killed father.

1219
01:13:39,416 --> 01:13:40,548
Linh and father going home...

1220
01:13:42,485 --> 01:13:45,153
There was big light.

1221
01:13:45,155 --> 01:13:47,588
Everything happened fast.

1222
01:13:47,590 --> 01:13:52,693
People yell, shoot gun.
Father hold linh tight.

1223
01:13:52,695 --> 01:13:54,128
Bo-tat run.

1224
01:13:54,130 --> 01:13:55,930
They shoot Bo-tat.

1225
01:13:58,935 --> 01:14:01,135
Father and linh land apart.

1226
01:14:01,137 --> 01:14:04,705
Father get up, run
to linh, and fall down.

1227
01:14:06,576 --> 01:14:07,909
He shot.

1228
01:14:07,911 --> 01:14:09,877
Linh not move.

1229
01:14:09,879 --> 01:14:11,913
Bo-tat save linh.

1230
01:14:11,915 --> 01:14:14,582
Men shoot Bo-tat more times.

1231
01:14:15,685 --> 01:14:18,486
Bo-tat no stop for many Miles.

1232
01:14:21,591 --> 01:14:23,191
Bo-tat save me.

1233
01:14:46,950 --> 01:14:48,916
Were you hurt?

1234
01:14:50,220 --> 01:14:52,253
You said you couldn't move.

1235
01:14:52,255 --> 01:14:55,790
No, I said I not move
because I too scared.

1236
01:14:55,792 --> 01:14:58,226
Father die because I not help him.
I scared.

1237
01:14:58,228 --> 01:14:59,760
No, no, linh, that's not why.

1238
01:14:59,762 --> 01:15:01,696
Yes, I scared!

1239
01:15:01,698 --> 01:15:02,763
Of course you were scared.

1240
01:15:02,765 --> 01:15:05,700
I'd be scared.
Anyone would be scared.

1241
01:15:05,702 --> 01:15:07,902
Linh.

1242
01:15:07,904 --> 01:15:08,836
It wasn't your fault.

1243
01:15:08,838 --> 01:15:10,771
Who fault?

1244
01:15:10,773 --> 01:15:11,939
People.

1245
01:15:14,711 --> 01:15:17,211
People far away, linh.

1246
01:15:18,515 --> 01:15:21,182
People who've never been here.

1247
01:15:21,184 --> 01:15:24,218
Linh no understand.

1248
01:15:32,595 --> 01:15:34,929
How did you get to ban don?

1249
01:15:34,931 --> 01:15:36,797
American take linh.

1250
01:15:36,799 --> 01:15:39,667
Said take linh back
to mountains someday.

1251
01:15:39,669 --> 01:15:42,837
Never did. Lie to linh.

1252
01:15:44,707 --> 01:15:47,208
I'm gonna take you
back to the mountains, linh.

1253
01:15:49,312 --> 01:15:51,712
I promise you.

1254
01:16:05,895 --> 01:16:08,629
Linh father was a good father.

1255
01:16:08,631 --> 01:16:10,731
Number one father.

1256
01:16:10,733 --> 01:16:12,867
I'm sure he was.

1257
01:16:24,914 --> 01:16:26,581
I'm sure he was.

1258
01:17:16,199 --> 01:17:17,398
Yeah.

1259
01:17:39,722 --> 01:17:42,356
Oh, man, I just went
to go take a whiz.

1260
01:17:43,893 --> 01:17:45,226
I didn't want to
desecrate the temple.

1261
01:17:45,228 --> 01:17:46,861
Forget about it. It's done.

1262
01:17:46,863 --> 01:17:48,896
He probably went to get
some food or something.

1263
01:17:48,898 --> 01:17:50,898
Whatever the reason, they're gonna
find out we're here pretty damn soon.

1264
01:17:50,900 --> 01:17:52,199
He's just a kid.

1265
01:17:52,201 --> 01:17:53,868
I know. I have to go get him.

1266
01:17:53,870 --> 01:17:56,337
I'll get the elephant to pleiku
and we'll meet you there.

1267
01:17:56,339 --> 01:17:57,972
Excuse me, guys, <i>una momento.</i>

1268
01:17:57,974 --> 01:17:59,974
But how are we gonna
move old Bo here, huh?

1269
01:17:59,976 --> 01:18:01,976
Linh taught farley
the basic commands.

1270
01:18:01,978 --> 01:18:03,878
No, he didn't.

1271
01:18:05,248 --> 01:18:06,414
Ok, sir, he did, but...

1272
01:18:08,851 --> 01:18:09,884
Take someone with you.

1273
01:18:09,886 --> 01:18:11,719
I screwed up. I'll go.

1274
01:18:21,364 --> 01:18:27,902
Th-that's funny. My... my
legs don't work.

1275
01:18:29,238 --> 01:18:30,971
Poole: Ah, hell. I'll go.

1276
01:18:33,743 --> 01:18:34,975
Kid's got my watch.

1277
01:19:16,753 --> 01:19:18,986
Ok, do the foot. Get... get her
to do the foot and get up.

1278
01:19:18,988 --> 01:19:20,287
Let's go.

1279
01:19:20,289 --> 01:19:21,288
Come on.

1280
01:19:21,290 --> 01:19:22,356
I don't... I don't know that one.

1281
01:19:22,358 --> 01:19:23,808
All right, can you
guys give me hand?

1282
01:19:23,809 --> 01:19:25,259
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Here' take the gun.
Take the gun.

1283
01:19:25,261 --> 01:19:27,461
Put your foot on my leg.

1284
01:19:27,463 --> 01:19:29,363
Ok. One... do you wanna jump in?

1285
01:19:29,365 --> 01:19:32,933
On 3, h.A., 1...2...3.

1286
01:19:36,272 --> 01:19:37,471
Ok, I'm up. I'm up.

1287
01:19:37,473 --> 01:19:39,306
Good job. Good job.

1288
01:19:39,308 --> 01:19:40,541
I don't know about this, sir.

1289
01:19:43,246 --> 01:19:44,378
I guess that means she's ready.

1290
01:19:44,380 --> 01:19:46,013
I think she's mad.
Doyle: Come on.

1291
01:19:51,354 --> 01:19:54,321
This way. Take us
around the village.

1292
01:19:55,424 --> 01:19:57,191
Farley, this way!

1293
01:19:57,193 --> 01:19:58,359
He didn't teach me how to turn.

1294
01:19:58,361 --> 01:19:59,927
Then stop her!

1295
01:19:59,929 --> 01:20:01,328
Ok, ok. Uh... Dee!

1296
01:20:03,348 --> 01:20:05,365
I mean... I mean,
Dee d'ng. D'ng. Dai!

1297
01:20:05,368 --> 01:20:06,433
Farley!

1298
01:20:06,435 --> 01:20:07,868
Uh!

1299
01:20:07,870 --> 01:20:08,969
Tell my mom I love her!

1300
01:20:17,280 --> 01:20:18,479
